    "guidance": "BoxLang AI ships with several built-in tools you can add to agents using the string shorthand 'toolName@bxai'. The most useful is webSearch@bxai, which gives your agent access to current information beyond its training cutoff.\n\nBuilt-in tools available:\n• webSearch@bxai — search the web (requires Brave/Tavily/Exa API key)\n• print@bxai — print debug output during agent execution\n• log@bxai — write to BoxLang log system\n• sendEmail@bxai — send email notifications\n\nFor webSearch, set your search provider API key in boxlang.json:\n{\n  \"modules\": { \"bxai\": { \"settings\": {\n    \"webSearch\": { \"provider\": \"brave\", \"apiKey\": \"${BRAVE_API_KEY}\" }\n  }}}\n}\n\nThis is one of the fastest ways to build a research assistant — the agent automatically decides when to search vs. answer from training data.",
    "output": "Based on my search results:\n\n**BoxLang AI v3.2.0** was released recently and includes:\n\n• New Agent Registry for managing named agents across your application\n• Built-in web search integration with Brave, Tavily, and Exa providers\n• Streaming support for class-based agents\n• Sub-agent hierarchy improvements with shared memory pools\n• MCP (Model Context Protocol) client support\n\nYou can install it with: `box install bx-ai` or `install-bx-module bx-ai`",
